{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":5,"timestamp":1772117733,"nonce":"DP4HmCy/wY0DOjA1cp6VU4YcK7Q=","metadata":{"github-id":"LE_lADOQ241x87uLpZEzwAAAAVhP-n-"},"added":["enhancement"],"removed":[]},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772127129,"nonce":"l3xjZnlsoic+sZ5Xt1VfbJE4nxI=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87shJgK","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/279#issuecomment-3968112650"},"message":"So, I like the idea of the research document that was generated for #249. I would like to consider formalizing a document like that that would periodically get updated and prunned. It could have a last modified stamp, that agents would check when consulting it, and warn the user if it becomes stale. (Maybe the stamp says, last modified so and so, if old, consider running the update research skill)\n\nNot all skill would consult this, but the brainstorming skill could use it as reference.","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772127556,"nonce":"L5d7rrqnth/Y46/fqCgTGfJdYx8=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87shS7U","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/279#issuecomment-3968151252"},"message":"## Triage Report\n\n### Scope Assessment\n\n**Well-scoped?** Loosely — intentionally open-ended for a creative tool, but makes acceptance criteria hard to verify.\n\n### Principle Alignment\n\n| Principle | Status | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| Only what's needed | **Question** | Agents brainstorm naturally in conversation. What does a skill add beyond consistently loading governance context? Is that enough for a dedicated skill vs. a section in plan-task? |\n| Human control and transparency | OK | Output stays in conversation |\n\n### Concerns\n\n1. **Value proposition unclear**: The skill's value is in consistently loading the right context (governance docs, principles, project knowledge) before brainstorming. But is that enough to justify a standalone skill?\n\n2. **Lifecycle placement**: Other skills operate on existing artifacts (issues, PRs, plans). Brainstorming is pre-lifecycle — exploratory thinking before an issue exists. Valid, but different workflow.\n\n3. **Testability**: \"Explores possibilities informed by principles\" is subjective — hard to verify in acceptance criteria.\n\n### Recommendations\n\n- Consider deferring until core lifecycle skills are proven and a specific gap is felt\n- If kept, sharpen the value: what context does the skill load that the agent wouldn't otherwise have?\n- Consider folding brainstorming guidance into plan-task rather than a standalone skill\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772130123,"nonce":"EUBH+5crDBu8Ue+yLaHxvduFb4Q=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87siPOu","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/279#issuecomment-3968398254"},"message":"## Refined Proposal: Research and Brainstorm Skills\n\nBased on discussion, this issue should be reworked from \"creative counterpart to evaluative skills\" to a concrete external research + brainstorming capability.\n\n### Concept\n\nTwo related skills that manage **external** knowledge (not project introspection) and apply it creatively.\n\n### research skill (`/research`)\n\nMaintains two living research digests — one for workspace concerns, one for project concerns. Each captures external best practices, emerging techniques, and relevant developments.\n\n**Digests:**\n- `.agent/knowledge/research_digest.md` — workspace research (git-tracked, benefits all projects)\n  - Agent workflow patterns, multi-framework coordination, CI/CD for AI agents, governance automation\n- `.agent/project_knowledge/research_digest.md` — project research (gitignored, project-specific)\n  - ROS 2 ecosystem, marine autonomy, hydrographic tech, sensor integration, domain developments\n\n**Modes:**\n- `/research --scope workspace \u003ctopic\u003e` — survey external sources, add to workspace digest\n- `/research --scope project \u003ctopic\u003e` — survey external sources, add to project digest\n- `/research --ingest \u003curl\u003e` — read a specific URL, extract relevant takeaways, append to appropriate digest\n- `/research --refresh` — re-survey known topics, prune stale entries, update timestamps\n\n**Digest format:**\n- Each entry: topic, date added, source links, key takeaways, relevance\n- Header with last-modified timestamp\n- Staleness note: \"If older than 30 days, consider running `/research --refresh`\"\n\n### brainstorm skill (`/brainstorm`)\n\nReads both research digests + project governance docs, explores possibilities for a given topic. This is where external research meets project context.\n\n- `/brainstorm \u003ctopic\u003e` — explore possibilities, identify gaps, suggest approaches\n- Output stays in conversation unless user asks otherwise\n- References specific digest entries when drawing on external research\n\n### Relationship to other skills\n\n- `research` produces the artifacts\n- `brainstorm` consumes them\n- Other lifecycle skills (review-issue, plan-task, review-pr) do **not** load the digests — too large and not relevant to their focused evaluations\n- `gather-project-knowledge` (#275) is project introspection; `research` is external survey — complementary, not overlapping\n\n### Open questions\n\n1. Should `/research --ingest \u003curl\u003e` auto-detect workspace vs project scope, or require `--scope`?\n2. What external sources should the skill survey by default? (ROS Discourse, GitHub trending, robotics conferences, etc.)\n3. Should the workspace digest be tracked (committed) or gitignored? Tracking means it's shared; gitignoring means each developer's agent builds their own view.\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null},{"type":4,"timestamp":1772143513,"nonce":"qF0UoBAICKKbt24aYnojjkvtY3I=","metadata":{"github-id":"CE_lADOQ241x87uLpZEzwAAAAVh9_fz"},"status":2}]}